%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be663f1aa2ac29ee31b374%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMedical%20care%20costs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20day%20care%20and%20preschool%20prices%2C%20have%20climbed%20a%20lot%20since%202000.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHealthcare%20and%20childcare%20will%20likely%20continue%20to%20be%20pricey%2C%20affecting%20people's%20savings%20and%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELimited%20options%20for%20automation%20in%20these%20care-related%20areas%20could%20be%20one%20reason.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20American%20who's%20taking%20care%20of%20young%20kids%20or%20older%20parents%20knows%20that%20childcare%20and%20healthcare%20are%20too%20expensive.%20And%20even%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-consumer-price-index-in-july-fed-interest-rates-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20broadly%20cools%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20the%20care%20industry%20is%20going%20to%20get%20more%20affordable%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20Jamele%2C%20Care.com's%20head%20of%20government%20affairs%20and%20public%20policy%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20US%20childcare%20costs%20%26quot%3Bhave%20been%20skyrocketing%2C%20and%20they're%20depleting%20the%20household%20incomes%20of%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da5547ac3f05e29175b4905007fd96bc3350a8e4da3423881286d18917d091262%26postID%3D66be575c7d61a86c18699e4b%26postSlug%3Dhealthcare-childcare-expensive-costs-wage-growth-employment-ai-risks-2024-8%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.care.com%252Fc%252Fhow-much-does-child-care-cost%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Care.com%20said%2035%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20a%202023%20survey%20of%20US%20adults%20said%20they%20dipped%20into%20their%20savings%20for%20care.%20Jamele%20pointed%20out%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkpmg.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Farticles%2F2024%2Fmay-2024-childcare-crisis-state-work-america.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20prices%20have%20surged%20more%20than%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20several%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20is%20also%20expensive%20and%20has%20seen%20prices%20climb%20faster%20than%20overall%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWRmZD%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Cumulative%20percent%20change%20in%20consumer%20prices%20since%202000%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20our%20members%20make%20trade-off%20decisions%20if%20healthcare%20costs%20are%20too%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20Pat%20Geraghty%2C%20CEO%20of%20insurance%20company%20GuideWell%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20some%20of%20the%20very%20basic%20needs%20in%20their%20life%20may%20get%20traded%20out%20because%20healthcare%20expenses%20are%20too%20high%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20focus%20needs%20to%20be%20on%20how%20to%20make%20healthcare%20affordable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20picture%20healthcare%20and%20childcare%20costs%20dramatically%20coming%20down%20anytime%20soon%20because%20so%20much%20of%20care%20work%20is%20labor-intensive.%20People%20are%20needed%20to%20care%20for%20children%20at%20day%20care%20centers%2C%20aging%20family%20members%20at%20assisted%20living%20and%20similar%20places%2C%20or%20patients%20at%20hospitals%2C%20and%20it's%20unlikely%20those%20tasks%20will%20be%20automated%20and%20handed%20over%20to%20robots%20or%20AI%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20care%20costs%20affect%20the%20people%20shelling%20out%20their%20money%20for%20these%20services%20and%20the%20workers%20who%20hope%20for%20higher%20pay.%20%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20raise%20wages%20because%20we%20cannot%20charge%20families%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Allyx%20Schiavone%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Friends%20Center%20for%20Children%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproviders-struggle-to-keep-funding-rising-childcare-costs-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc3b4457-4dd0-4353-ac13-8dfbdc0f6c4d%5C%22%3EWhy%20childcare%20and%20healthcare%20costs%20have%20surged%20and%20could%20continue%20to%20be%20pricey%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChildcare%20and%20healthcare%20costs%20have%20soared%20since%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%2C%20while%20televisions%20and%20wireless%20phone%20services%20have%20plunged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%202000%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20TVs%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20toys%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cellphone%20service%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20software%20%E2%80%94%20those%20have%20all%20fallen%20a%20lot%20either%20because%20of%20automation%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20manufacturing%20TVs%20and%20toys%2C%20or%20because%20of%20scalability%20because%20of%20these%20natural%20monopolies%20and%20these%20very%20high%20fixed%20costs%20but%20tiny%20marginal%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Julia%20Pollak%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20technologies%20like%20software%20and%20cellphone%20service%20that%20scale%20and%20allow%20companies%20to%20charge%20less%20and%20less%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Pollak%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20cost%20of%20services%20that%20cannot%20be%20automated%26quot%3B%20and%20scaled%20have%20been%20labor%20intensive%20and%20have%20seen%20prices%20skyrocket.%20That%20would%20include%20some%20costs%20related%20to%20healthcare%20and%20childcare.%20Pollak%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHospital%20services%2C%20medical%20care%2C%20childcare%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cost%20of%20all%20those%20have%20grown%20dramatically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollak%20said%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20probably%20lessen%20the%20costs%20for%20tech%20and%20other%20services%20but%20likely%20won't%20be%20the%20case%20for%20healthcare%20and%20childcare.%20Still%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20AI%20can%20help%20lessen%20care%20costs.%20Geraghty%20pointed%20out%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20AI%20tools%20in%20radiology%20detecting%20disease%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildcare%20and%20healthcare%20have%20also%20seen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteacher-shortage-schools-nurses-daycare-costs-inflation-rate-retail-workers-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-helping-health-insurers-doctors-with-administrative-tasks-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20and%20automation%20could%20be%20helpful%20in%20these%20sectors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20likely%20still%20will%20be%20demand%20for%20new%20workers.%20For%20instance%2C%20childcare%20providers%20are%20typically%20required%20to%20have%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eminimum%20ratio%20of%20caregiving%20staff%20to%20children%20under%20their%20supervision.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESome%20healthcare%20jobs%20could%20be%20at%20risk%20from%20AI%2C%20but%20as%20the%20population%20ages%2C%20healthcare%20will%20need%20people%20in%20care%20and%20other%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20about%20whether%20things%20can%20be%20done%20with%20the%20help%20of%20automation%20that's%20affecting%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20things%20happening%20in%20the%20healthcare%20sector%20like%20private%20equity%20coming%20in%20and%20buying%20physician%20offices%2C%26quot%3B%20Geraghty%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20do%20that%2C%20they%20want%20a%20return%2C%20and%20their%20desire%20to%20get%20a%20return%20pushes%20the%20cost%20of%20healthcare%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Pollak%20said%20the%20widening%20of%20remote%20work%20outside%20healthcare%20and%20childcare%20could%20mean%20the%20costs%20for%20these%20two%20types%20of%20care%20increase.%20%26quot%3BIn%20order%20to%20compete%2C%20those%20on-site%20employers%20in%20day%20care%20services%20and%20hospitals%20need%20to%20pay%20workers%20more%20to%20veer%20them%20away%20from%20jobs%20that%20are%20more%20flexible%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20how%20to%20do%20exactly%20that%20while%20also%20being%20able%20to%20pay%20operating%20costs.%20Jamele%20said%20it's%20expensive%20to%20run%20childcare%20centers%2C%20including%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20people%20working%20and%20trying%20to%20offer%20competitive%20pay.%20%26quot%3BI've%20heard%20anecdotally%20as%20well%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20childcare%20workers%20are%20leaving%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOther%20jobs%20in%20retail%20are%20paying%20more%20in%20some%20cases%20in%20some%20states.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22556cb6bd-eaeb-4e72-acfe-162e0c2ca5a0%5C%22%3EWages%20and%20prices%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInflationary%20pressure%20on%20wages%20over%20the%20past%20two%20(2)%20years%20has%20driven%20the%20cost%20of%20healthcare%20and%20childcare%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Hamilton%2C%20Gallagher's%20global%20chairman%20of%20human%20resources%20and%20compensation%20consulting%2C%20said%20in%20a%20written%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThese%20increased%20costs%20are%20both%20being%20passed%20on%20through%20increases%20in%20health%20insurance%20premiums%20to%20employers%20as%20well%20as%20higher%20prices%20of%20daycare%20and%20after-school%20care%20for%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20just%20a%20year%2C%20childcare%20costs%20have%20increased%20on%20average.%20Care.com's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da5547ac3f05e29175b4905007fd96bc3350a8e4da3423881286d18917d091262%26postID%3D66be575c7d61a86c18699e4b%26postSlug%3Dhealthcare-childcare-expensive-costs-wage-growth-employment-ai-risks-2024-8%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.care.com%252Fc%252Fhow-much-does-child-care-cost%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20Cost%20of%20Care%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20average%20day%20care%20costs%20have%20surged%20for%20an%20infant%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%24284%20a%20week%20in%202022%20to%20%24321%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20in%20the%20childcare%20services%20sector%20are%20seeing%20higher%20earnings%20than%20the%20same%20month%20a%20year%20prior%2C%20just%20like%20workers%20in%20healthcare.%20These%20two%20sectors%20have%20seen%20wage%20growth%20outpace%20inflation.%20While%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20rose%203.0%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20June%2C%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20rose%205.2%25%20for%20the%20childcare%20services%20sector%20and%203.6%25%20for%20the%20healthcare%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20that%20robust%20wage%20growth%20in%20childcare%2C%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20for%20this%20sector%20are%20low%20compared%20to%20the%20overall%20figure%20for%20private%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20%2420.87%20an%20hour%20for%20childcare%20services%20in%20June%20compared%20to%20%2434.99%20for%20total%20private%20employees.%20The%20healthcare%20sector's%20average%20in%20June%20was%20%2437.57.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3DU42%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Cumulative%20percent%20change%20in%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20since%202021%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22481%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EJamele%20said%20the%20US%20childcare%20system%20should%20be%20reimagined%2C%20including%20modernizing%20and%20enhancin