pping%20inside%20TapOut%20Sports%20Zone%20Bar%20and%20Grill%20in%20Boquete%2C%20Panama%2C%20is%20like%20stepping%20inside%20suburban%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20menu%20features%20American%20staples%20like%20cheeseburgers%2C%20barbecue%20chicken%20sandwiches%2C%20and%20Philly%20cheesesteaks.%20Flat-screen%20TVs%20sit%20above%20the%20bar%2C%20airing%20the%20latest%20game.%20On%20Friday%20nights%2C%20you%20might%20catch%20a%20band%20performing%20hits%20like%20%26quot%3BTake%20It%20Easy%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20Eagles.%20On%20Mondays%2C%20locals%20stop%20by%20for%20karaoke%20and%20%241%20beers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visited%20TapOut%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20not%20for%20the%20bacon-wrapped%20shrimp%20but%20to%20see%20the%20Boquete%20Community%20Players%2C%20a%20theater%20group%20that%20hosts%20shows%20in%20the%20back%20room%20of%20the%20restaurant.%20On%20a%20Saturday%20afternoon%2C%20the%20small%20room%20was%20bustling%20with%20a%20dozen%20Americans%20preparing%20for%20an%20upcoming%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20debated%20curtain%20colors%20and%20stage%20lighting%2C%20a%20waiter%20dropped%20off%20a%20round%20of%20pi%C3%B1a%20coladas.%20Another%20passed%20by%20with%20two%20bottles%20of%20Panama%20Light%20beer.%20Since%20arriving%20at%20TapOut%2C%20it%20was%20the%20first%20reminder%20that%20I%20was%20far%20from%20the%20heart%20of%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TapOut%20Sports%20Zone%20in%20Boquete%2C%20Panama.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6697d3da8893442a515750a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETapOut%20Sports%20Zone%20in%20Boquete%2C%20Panama.%3Cp%3EMonica%20Humphries%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20around%20retirement%20age%20%E2%80%94%20is%20standard%20in%20Boquete.%20The%20town's%20year-round%20cool%20temperatures%20and%20the%20affordable%20cost%20of%20living%20have%20earned%20it%20recognition%20for%20being%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-ten-countries-for-a-comfortable-retirement-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20places%20to%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20people%20moved%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-moving-abroad-cost-of-living-too-expensive-debt-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretiring%20in%20the%20US%20was%20too%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20impossible%20%E2%80%94%20others%20told%20me%20they%20came%20to%20avoid%20America's%20divisive%20political%20climate.%20Regardless%20of%20why%20they%20ended%20up%20in%20Boquete%2C%20the%20town%20has%20changed%20drastically%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20because%20of%20retirees%2C%20and%20the%20influx%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20slowing%20down%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBoquete%20wasn't%20always%20a%20retiree's%20paradise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%201911%2C%20Boquete%20remained%20a%20quiet%20town%20for%20decades.%20The%20region%20was%20known%20for%20its%20coffee%20plantations%20and%20an%20annual%20flower%20festival.%20Beyond%20beans%20and%20blooms%2C%20Panamanians%20were%20lured%20to%20Boquete%20for%20its%20comfortable%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESituated%20about%204%2C000%20feet%20above%20sea%20level%2C%20Boquete's%20temperatures%20hover%20around%2070%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20year-round.%20The%20town%20has%20long%20been%20a%20weekend%20escape%20for%20Panamanians%20living%20in%20nearby%20cities%20like%20David%2C%20where%20temperatures%20can%20reach%20the%2090s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThalia%20Velasquez%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20David%2C%20remembers%20begging%20her%20mom%20to%20take%20her%20to%20Boquete%20every%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoquete%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20was%20a%20very%2C%20very%20simple%2C%20little%20town%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20told%20me%20about%20her%20childhood%20visits%20there.%20%26quot%3BThe%20stores%20would%20close%20by%204%20p.m.%20The%20bakery%20would%20close%20by%205%20or%206%20p.m.%2C%20maybe%20even%20earlier.%20There%20were%20very%20few%20cars%20in%20town.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20still%20rode%20their%20horses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandreth%20Laws%2C%20who%20owns%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fiwannaboquete%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIwanna%20Boquete%20Tours%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20similar%20memories%20from%20growing%20up%20in%20Boquete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20Boquete%2C%20Panama.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6697d4009caa6ed01e0253b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOld%20pictures%20of%20Boquete%2C%20Panama%2C%20hang%20in%20the%20town's%20library.%3Cp%3EMonica%20Humphries%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2042-year-old%20said%20the%20town's%20busiest%20time%20was%20during%20an%20annual%20flower%20festival.%20He%20remembers%20his%20family%20home%20teeming%20with%20people.%20There%20weren't%20enough%20hotels%20in%20town%20to%20accommodate%20visitors%20in%20the%20'80s%20and%20'90s.%20Back%20then%2C%20there%20were%20few%20tourists%20and%20even%20fewer%20foreign%20retirees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201990s%2C%20Velasquez%20took%20her%20partner%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Samuel%20Walker%20Taliaferro%2C%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20Panama.%20They%20stopped%20in%20Boquete%2C%20and%20Taliaferro%2C%20an%20American%20inventor%2C%20engineer%2C%20and%20investor%2C%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20moved%20to%20Boquete%2C%20along%20with%20Velasquez's%20two%20children%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20opened%20a%20real-estate%20business%2C%20bought%20land%2C%20and%20spent%20their%20days%20riding%20horses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20one%20ride%2C%20Taliaferro%20took%20her%20Velasquez%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.valleescondidoboquete.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EValle%20Escondido%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20coffee%20plantation%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20beautiful%20place%20in%20the%20valley%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20said.%20The%20couple%20bought%20the%20land%2C%20and%20Taliaferro%20eventually%20transformed%20it%20into%20a%20%24100%20million%20residential%20resort%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20property%20opened%20in%202003%2C%20with%20a%20chapel%2C%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20restaurant%2C%20hotel%2C%20and%20150%20condominiums.%20Taliaferro%20set%20out%20to%20promote%20both%20his%20property%20and%20Boquete%20as%20a%20retirement%20haven.%20He%20worked%20with%20International%20Living%20magazine%20to%20advertise%20the%20destination%2C%20and%20retirees%20arrived%20with%20suitcases%20in%20tow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20helped%20when%20AARP%20named%20Boquete%20the%20No.%201%20foreign%20retirement%20destination%20in%20the%20Western%20Hemisphere.%20In%202005%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoney.cnn.com%2Fmagazines%2Ffortune%2Ffortune_archive%2F2005%2F07%2F11%2F8265242%2Findex.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFortune%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20featured%20the%20town%20as%20an%20idyllic%20place%20to%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTaliaferro%20sold%20Boquete%20like%20a%20new%20destination%2C%20like%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20beautiful%20places%20to%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%2C%20who%20worked%20for%20Taliaferro%20as%20a%20bartender%20in%202003%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20pushed%20Boquete%20to%20be%20the%20best.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVelasquez%20said%20she%20initially%20feared%20backlash%20from%20locals%20and%20admitted%20some%20people%20were%20upset%20by%20the%20town's%20quick%20change.%20Others%20saw%20it%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20create%20their%20own%20businesses%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20new%20residents%20and%20visitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20Boquete%20was%20home%20to%2017%2C000%20people%2C%20according%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citypopulation.de%2Fen%2Fpanama%2Fadmin%2Fchiriqu%25C3%25AD%2F0404__boquete%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20City%20Population%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202023%2C%20the%20town%20ballooned%20to%2023%2C500%20residents.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finternationalliving.com%2Fbuilding-a-better-life-on-2500-a-month-in-boquete%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Living%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%205%2C000%2C%20or%20about%20a%20fifth%20of%20the%20population%2C%20are%20expats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20billboard%20advertising%20one%20of%20dozens%20of%20new%20projects%20being%20developed%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20Panama%20in%202008.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66be4409955b01c3294eff5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20billboard%20advertising%20one%20of%20dozens%20of%20new%20projects%20being%20developed%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20Panama%20in%202008.%3Cp%3EBoston%20Globe%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThousands%20of%20expats%20now%20call%20Boquete%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20hopscotched%20between%20Boquete's%20roads%20and%20uneven%20sidewalks%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20beauty%20and%20change%20Laws%20and%20Velasquez%20described.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%20town%20sits%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20a%20valley%20where%20the%20outline%20of%20mountains%20can%20be%20spotted%20in%20every%20direction.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20greenest%20places%20I've%20visited%3A%20tropical%20flowers%20fill%20gardens%20outside%20family-owned%20restaurants%2C%20and%20massive%20palm%20fronds%20reach%20toward%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20green%20landscapes%2C%20I%20also%20saw%20foreign%20retirees'%20influence%20on%20Boquete.%20I%20doubted%20the%20sandwich%20shop%20Holy%20Cow%20Boquete%20or%20Panama%20Barcade%20existed%20when%20Laws%20grew%20up.%20Traffic%20sometimes%20clogged%20the%20main%20street.%20Signs%20hung%20in%20the%20library%20advertising%20an%20upcoming%20talk%20on%20cybersecurity%20and%20another%20discussion%20on%20wills%20%E2%80%94%20topics%20seemingly%20fit%20for%20an%20older%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoquete%20is%20still%20a%20small%20Panamanian%20town.%20Walmarts%20and%20McDonalds%20have%20yet%20to%20reach%20the%20serene%20valley%20and%20Spanish%20was%20the%20language%20I%20heard%20most.%20But%20walk%20down%20any%20street%2C%20and%20older%20Americans%20are%20impossible%20to%20miss.%20They're%20also%20eager%20to%20share%20how%20they%20ended%20up%20in%20Boquete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackie%20Lange%2C%2070%2C%20moved%20to%20the%20town%20in%202010%20to%20escape%20the%20Texas%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelle%20Sparta%2C%2054%2C%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Jeff%20Brandon%2C%20arrived%20in%20Boquete%20in%202022%2C%20citing%20tension%20and%20high%20stress%20levels%20from%20America's%20political%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Hill%20was%20ready%20to%20retire%2C%20but%20early%20retirement%20in%20California%20was%20out%20of%20reach.%20Faced%20with%20working%20until%20his%20full%20Social%20Security%20hit%20at%2067%2C%20Hill%20and%20his%20wife%20decided%20to%20relocate%20somewhere%20cheaper%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TapOut%20Sports%20Zone%20in%20Boquete%2C%20Panama.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6697d4005439fb59cebe14a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20dance%20to%20a%20band%20playing%20at%20TapOut%20Sports%20Zone%20in%20Boquete%2C%20Panama.%3Cp%3EMonica%20Humphries%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20expat%20I%20spoke%20with%20had%20a%20different%20reason%20for%20the%20initial%20push%20to%20move%20to%20Boquete%2C%20but%20they%20all%20mentioned%20similar%20motives%20for%20staying.%20Mild%20temperatures%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cost-of-living-what-is-middle-class-housing-market-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20living%20is%20cheaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20healthcare%20is%20affordable%2C%20the%20economy%20uses%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20no%20one%20talks%20about%20politics%2C%20and%20you%20can%20get%20by%20only%20speaking%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoquete%20is%20also%20home%20to%20tour%20companies%20showing%20off%20the%20technicolor%20landscape%2C%20grocery%20stores%2C%20and%20nearby%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELange%20owns%20one%20of%20those%20companies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpanamarelocationtours.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPanama%20Relocation%20Tours%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20takes%20groups%20to%20meet%20with%20immigration%20lawyers%20to%20discuss%20visa%20options.%20For%20many%20retirees%2C%20getting%20residency%20in%20Panama%20is%20easy%20with%20the%20pensionado%20visa%2C%20which%20requires%20proof%20of%20income%20or%20a%20pension%20of%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20and%20an%20additional%20%24250%20for%20each%20dependant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%241%2C000%20is%20required%2C%20realistically%2C%20retirees%20can%20comfortably%20live%20in%20Boquete%20for%20%241%2C400%20a%20month%20as%20an%20individual%20or%20%242%2C000%20as%20a%20couple%2C%20Lange%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20drastically%20less%20than%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-states-to-retire-in-cost-of-living-comfortably-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20cheapest%20US%20state%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gobankingrates.com%2Fretirement%2Fplanning%2Fhow-much-a-comfortable-retirement-will-cost-you-in-each-state%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20analysis%20by%20GOBankingRates%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Mississippi%20had%20the%20lowest%20cost%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement%20at%20%2462%2C154%20annually%2C%20or%20%245%2C180%20a%20month.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Americans%20living%20in%20places%20like%20California%20and%20New%20York%20need%20closer%20to%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20ex-pats%20meeting%20up%20through%20Panama%20Relocation%20Tours.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66991fb380d4d5da13d4e37e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20group%20of%20ex-pats%20meeting%20up%20through%20Panama%20Relocation%20Tours.%3Cp%3EJackie%20Lange%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELange%20estimates%20that%20her%20team%20helps%20about%20100%20people%20move%20to%20Panama%20monthly.%20And%20it's%20not%20just%20Boquete%2C%20Panama%20City%20and%20the%20San%20Carlos%20area%20are%20also%20popular%20retiree%20destinations%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECheap%20living%20is%20not%20so%20cheap%20anymore%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDagmar%20Rios%20grew%20up%20taking%20family%20trips%20to%20Boquete.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20time%2C%20it%20was%20more%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20and%20working%20in%20Panama%20City%2C%20Rios%2C%2034%2C%20moved%20to%20Boquete%20in%202018.%20She%20bought%20a%20house%20and%20eventually%20opened%20her%20own%20dentist's%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoquete%20is%20drastically%20different%20from%20Rios'%20childhood%20memories%2C%20but%20she%20said%20she's%20also%20seen%20many%20changes%20in%20the%20town%20in%20the%20six%20years%20she's%20lived%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20there%20are%20more%20supermarkets.%20Now%2C%20there%20are%20more%20restaurants%20and%20hotels%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20these%20changes%2C%20Rios%20said%20costs%20have%20increased.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20person%20could%20afford%20a%20house%20with%20a%20monthly%20salary%20of%20%24600.%20Rios%20said%20her%20employees%20tell%20