20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFHXsC6TOgY%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFHXsC6TOgY%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20(%40elonmusk)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1825738817275383950%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2020%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20it%20will%20not%20look%20blue%2C%20as%20the%20third%20full%20moon%20in%20a%20season%20with%20four%20full%20Moons%2C%20this%20will%20be%20a%20Blue%20Moon.%20The%20first%20recorded%20use%20of%20%26quot%3BBlue%20Moon%26quot%3B%20in%20English%20dates%20from%201528%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gordon%20Johnston%2C%20retired%20NASA%20Programme%20Executive%2C%20in%20an%20earlier%20blog%20post%20on%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201979%20astrologer%20Richard%20Nolle%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bsupermoon%26quot%3B%20as%20either%20a%20new%20or%20full%20Moon%20that%20occurs%20when%20the%20Moon%20is%20within%2090%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20closest%20approach%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20%26quot%3BBlue%20Moon%26quot%3B%20has%20since%20the%201940s%2C%20also%20been%20used%20for%20the%20second%20full%20Moon%20in%20a%20month%20that%20has%20two%20full%20Moons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2024%20will%20witness%20four%20consecutive%20supermoons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20supermoon%20occurring%20next%2C%20on%20September%2017%2C%20is%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Harvest%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20also%20be%20partially%20eclipsed%20by%20Earth%20during%20the%20night%20as%20a%20portion%20of%20it%20passes%20into%20Earth's%20shadow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20full%20moon%20of%20the%20year%20is%20expected%20to%20shine%20bright%20on%20October%2017.%20Known%20as%20Hunter's%20Moon%2C%20it%20will%20also%20be%20the%20closest%20full%20moon%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20last%20supermoon%20of%20the%20year%20will%20occur%20on%20November%2015.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this