e-owned%20708th%20Shipbuilding%20Research%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20August%208%20that%20it's%20planning%20something%20new%20to%20meet%20the%20local%20coast%20guard's%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20operate%20in%20the%20far%20seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20else%20about%20the%20project%20was%20revealed.%20The%20announcement%20only%20said%20the%20institute%20had%20debuted%20the%20ship's%20design%20at%20a%20coast%20guard%20equipment%20conference%20in%20Zhejiang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shipbuilder%20said%20the%20vessel%20was%20designed%20according%20to%20%26quot%3Bsystem%20and%20mission%20requirements%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20coast%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Chinese%20words%20for%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20are%20also%20the%20words%20used%20for%20%26quot%3Bcarrier%2C%26quot%3B%20leading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbaijiahao.baidu.com%2Fs%3Fid%3D1807422496324243499%26wfr%3Dspider%26for%3Dpc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20bloggers%20to%20discuss%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20earnest%20what%20the%20new%20vessel%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20law%20enforcement%20agency%20running%20a%20carrier-equivalent%20ship%20would%20be%20unprecedented%20in%20a%20world%20where%20coast%20guards%20typically%20rely%20on%20smaller%2C%20faster%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20China%20has%20recently%20been%20looking%20into%20bigger%20and%20bolder%20vessels%20for%20its%20coast%20guard%20that%20are%20strikingly%20similar%20to%20its%20naval%20assets%2C%20indicating%20that%20Beijing%20has%20ambitious%20plans%20for%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20summer%2C%20it%20sent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeijings-monster-coastguard-ship-ramps-up-tensions-south-china-sea-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20new%20gigantic%20%26quot%3Bmonster%20ships%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20startling%20its%20neighbors.%20Each%20displaces%2012%2C000%20tons%20and%20is%20541%20feet%20long%2C%20or%20three%20times%20the%20size%20of%20the%20US%20Coast%20Guard's%20cutters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSize%20does%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Michael%20Dahm%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20intelligence%20officer%20and%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20for%20Aerospace%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BA%20vessel's%20size%20and%20displacement%20often%20translate%20directly%20into%20capabilities.%20A%20bigger%20ship%20means%20more%20people%2C%20more%20weapons%2C%20more%20fuel%2C%20more%20endurance%2C%20more%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.163.com%2Fdy%2Farticle%2FJ9G7T7JM0515CA2O.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESome%20bloggers%3C%2Fa%3E%20speculated%20that%20the%20new%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20could%20be%20an%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20though%20China's%20coast%20guard%20rarely%20uses%20manned%20planes%20for%20its%20daily%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20likely%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmil.sohu.com%2Fa%2F799969564_100092631%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eothers%20posited%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20Beijing%20is%20planning%20a%20drone%20platform%20or%20helicopter%20landing%20dock%20that%20can%20sail%20on%20the%20high%20seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207f342e2-8828-4941-afc5-f1f37be0adf0%5C%22%3EThe%20world's%20first%20drone%20carriers%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20photos%20or%20videos%20of%20the%20design%2C%20international%20experts%20can%20only%20guess%20what%20form%20the%20ship%20will%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaritime%20drone%20platforms%20are%20still%20a%20novel%20concept%2C%20but%20there%20are%20signs%20that%20China%20is%20building%20at%20least%20one.%20In%20May%2C%20Dahm%20identified%20a%20large%20Chinese%20ship%20under%20construction%20at%20a%20Jiangsu%20shipyard%2C%20which%20he%20said%20is%20likely%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2024%2F05%2Fchina-builds-worlds-first-dedicated-drone-carrier%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20first%20dedicated%20drone%20carrier.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20shipyard%20is%20run%20by%20a%20different%20shipbuilder%2C%20so%20there's%20no%20evidence%20that%20this%20Jiangsu%20carrier%20is%20related%20to%20the%20coast%20guard%20%26quot%3Bmothership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Dahm%2C%20it's%20not%20yet%20clear%20if%20this%20new%20coast%20guard%20vessel%20is%20even%20equivalent%20to%20a%20carrier%20in%20function%20or%20tonnage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20often%20surprised%20by%20how%20right%20Chinese%20bloggers%20can%20be%20about%20these%20sorts%20of%20things%2C%20but%20in%20this%20case%2C%20I%20think%20they%20may%20be%20overselling%20'mothership%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20708th%20Shipbuilding%20Research%20Institute%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20would%20provide%20%26quot%3Bcomprehensive%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Dahm%20believes%20smaller%20Chinese%20coast%20guard%20vessels%20could%20fit%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Chinese%20are%20trying%20to%20create%20more%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Collin%20Koh%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20Defence%20and%20Strategic%20Studies%20at%20Singapore's%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoh%20also%20thinks%20the%20%26quot%3Bmothership%26quot%3B%20is%20more%20likely%20a%20drone%20carrier%2C%20at%20about%2010%2C000%20to%2020%2C000%20tons%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20full-size%20aircraft%20carrier%20at%2085%2C000%20tons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223390%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20drone%20photo%20taken%20on%20May%201%20shows%20China's%20third%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian%2C%20during%20its%20maiden%20sea%20trials.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c2f91e1aa2ac29ee3217a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222260%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina%20has%20three%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20each%20displacing%20about%2060%2C000%20to%2085%2C000%20tons.%3Cp%3EPu%20Haiyang%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20coast%20guard%20already%20has%20a%20large%20fleet%20of%20more%20than%20200%20patrolling%20vessels.%20But%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20further%20contest%20territory%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20%E2%80%94%20its%20most%20high-profile%20area%20of%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20it%20has%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20efficiently%20repair%20and%20resupply%20its%20ships%20at%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20drone%20carrier%20could%20circumvent%20that%20issue%2C%20Koh%20said%2C%20allowing%20Beijing%20to%20maintain%20a%2024%2F7%20presence%20by%20deploying%20in%20a%20central%20location%20and%20sending%20out%20the%20drones%20repeatedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20put%20drones%20and%20small%20craft%20into%20a%20very%20strategic%20area%2C%20it%20could%20have%20a%20pretty%20big%20coverage.%20That's%20likely%20the%20Chinese%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20Koh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Japan%20is%20planning%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjapannews.yomiuri.co.jp%2Fpolitics%2Fdefense-security%2F20240608-190811%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilarly%20massive%20coast%20guard%20vessel%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20says%20will%20displace%20some%2030%2C000%20tons%20and%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Boffshore%20base%26quot%3B%20for%20other%20ships.%20The%20largest%20ship%20in%20its%20current%20coast%20guard%20fleet%20is%206%2C500%20tons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a8bd2f80-74c1-4fa2-96ca-15b1bf05cfb8%5C%22%3EChina%20saying%20'far%20seas'%20could%20be%20a%20clue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20708th's%20description%20of%20its%20new%20vessel%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bfar%20seas%26quot%3B%20support%20ship%20also%20indicates%20that%20Beijing%20may%20have%20plans%20to%20use%20its%20coast%20guard%20further%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%2C%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%2C%20promoted%20the%20idea%20of%20defending%20its%20interests%20overseas%20with%20naval%20assets%2C%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20the%20US%20Navy%20patrols%20waters%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20part%20of%20its%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20strategy%2C%20China%20seems%20to%20be%20growing%20the%20role%20and%20presence%20of%20its%20coast%20guard%20in%20the%20South%20Pacific%2C%20after%20doing%20the%20same%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Benjamin%20Blandin%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20network%20coordinator%20at%20the%20Yokosuka%20Council%20on%20Asia-Pacific%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20there%20is%20a%20big%20step%20from%20planning%20to%20operational%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20China%20still%20needs%20a%20network%20of%20ports%20and%20resupply%20points%20to%20operate%20efficiently%20on%20the%20high%20seas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDahm%20said%20China%20will%20have%20an%20easier%20time%20putting%20its%20ships%20in%20foreign%20territory%20if%20they're%20painted%20in%20coast%20guard%20livery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20coast%20guard%20vessels%20working%20with%20host%20nation%20law%20enforcement%20is%20a%20much%20better%20look%20for%20China%20than%20a%20big%20gray%20warship%20bristling%20with%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20international%20press%20center%20for%20China's%20foreign%20ministry%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-mothership-coast-guard-drone-aircraft-carrier-south-sea-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724118767000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c2fa53b4912df3ae1c889a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-mothership-coast-g